				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6339435#post-3913974</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6339435/an-o5-s-sleepless-night#post-3913974</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 Aug 2018 00:23:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>stormbreath</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3075960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I love this. There are some lines that read a bit oddly, most notably this, which really wants to be two separate sentences:</p> <blockquote> <p>I guess I won’t have to worry if it’s real or not since I’m not going there anyway, maybe I have a chance at one of the non-human afterlives with the amount of “deities” I’ve angered.</p> </blockquote> <p>But I'm a big fan of the depiction of the O5 Council presented here, in addition to the characterization of the narrator. His plan isn't really spiteful - it's more the cost that the Devourer will need to pay to eat our world.</p> <p>Very nice characterization, and a good narrative.</p> <p>+1.</p> <p>My favorite number.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
